President Biden and President Erdogan met at the G20 Summit and discussed various topics. President Biden offered his condolences to President Erdogan and the people of Turkey regarding the recent acts of violence in Istanbul. He also reaffirmed the United States' support for its NATO ally. President Biden expressed appreciation for President Erdogan's efforts in renewing the Black Sea Grain Initiative, which has been important in improving global food security amidst Russia's conflict. The two leaders also talked about coordinating closely on NATO Alliance issues and other regional and global concerns.